那他还要穿什么呢？

52
00:02:20,920 --> 00:02:23,280
Well, we need to keep our fingers warm.
嗯，我们需要让手指保暖。

53
00:02:23,280 --> 00:02:27,320
So there are two kinds of ways to keep your fingers warm.
有两种方法可以让手指保暖。

54
00:02:27,320 --> 00:02:32,120
And the way in this dialogue that the boy keeps his fingers warm is with mittens.
在这个对话里，男孩让手指保暖的方式是戴连指手套。

55
00:02:32,120 --> 00:02:35,200
All right, so mittens you put on your hands.
好的，连指手套是戴在手上的。

56
00:02:35,200 --> 00:02:38,840
Now what's the difference between mittens and gloves?
那连指手套和分指手套有什么区别呢？

57
00:02:38,840 --> 00:02:42,360
Okay, gloves have special places for each finger.
好的，分指手套每个手指都有单独的位置。

58
00:02:42,360 --> 00:02:44,880
One, two, three, four, five on each hand.
每只手有五个手指，一个、两个、三个、四个、五个。

59
00:02:44,880 --> 00:02:50,800
And mittens, there's two spaces, one for your thumb and one for all your other fingers.
而连指手套有两个空间，一个给大拇指，另一个给其他所有手指。

60
00:02:50,800 --> 00:02:52,920
So that means you can't really hold things.
所以这意味着你不太能拿东西。

61
00:02:52,920 --> 00:02:55,000
So you kind of look like a penguin or something like that.
所以你看起来有点像企鹅之类的。

62
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:58,320
Yeah, you look like a, yeah, exactly like a penguin.
是啊，看起来就像，对，就像企鹅。

63
00:02:58,320 --> 00:03:00,120
And it's mostly for children.
而且这主要是给小孩用的。

64
00:03:00,120 --> 00:03:05,840
Adults don't wear mittens because adults need to hold things like keys and phones and car
大人不戴连指手套，因为大人需要拿东西，比如钥匙、手机和汽车

65
00:03:05,840 --> 00:03:07,080
steering wheels.
方向盘。

66
00:03:07,080 --> 00:03:09,640
So in this case, mittens is usually for children.
所以在这种情况下，连指手套通常是给小孩的。

67
00:03:09,640 --> 00:03:11,880
Okay, so mittens.
好的，所以是连指手套。

68
00:03:11,880 --> 00:03:14,080
And well, the mother is still a little bit worried.
嗯，妈妈还是有点担心。

69
00:03:14,080 --> 00:03:16,880
So she tells him to wear a scarf.
所以她让他戴上围巾。

70
00:03:16,880 --> 00:03:23,900
Okay, a scarf is a long, usually made of wool, a long piece of fabric that you put around
好的，围巾是一条长长的，通常由羊毛制成，一块长条布料，你把它围在

71
00:03:23,900 --> 00:03:25,840
your neck to keep your neck warm.
脖子上，让脖子保暖。

72
00:03:25,840 --> 00:03:27,400
Okay, so a scarf.
好的，所以是围巾。

73
00:03:27,400 --> 00:03:28,400
A scarf.
围巾。

74
00:03:28,400 --> 00:03:34,200
Okay, and he's put on the mittens, the scarf, the hat, and he's missing some earmuffs.
好的，他戴上了连指手套、围巾、帽子，还缺个耳罩。

75
00:03:34,200 --> 00:03:39,840
Okay, this is a little funny because usually if you're wearing a hat, you don't need earmuffs.
好的，这有点好笑，因为通常如果你戴了帽子，就不需要耳罩了。

76
00:03:39,840 --> 00:03:44,560
But earmuffs are like headphones, but they keep your ears warm.
但耳罩像耳机一样，但它们能让耳朵保暖。

77
00:03:44,560 --> 00:03:48,560
And we wear these, they don't cover your head, they just cover your ears.
我们戴这个，它们不盖住头，只盖住耳朵。

78
00:03:48,560 --> 00:03:51,240
And usually they're just two round circles over your ears.
通常就是两个圆形的圈盖在耳朵上。

79
00:03:51,240 --> 00:03:56,240
So as you say, exactly, they look like big earphones and they keep your ears warm.
所以就像你说的，没错，它们看起来像大耳机，能让耳朵保暖。

80
00:03:56,240 --> 00:04:00,520
Now, as you say, you usually don't wear this if you're wearing a hat because, well, you
现在，就像你说的，如果你戴了帽子，通常不会戴这个，因为，嗯，你

81
00:04:00,520 --> 00:04:02,280
would put your ears inside your hat, right?
会把耳朵塞进帽子里，对吧？

82
00:04:02,280 --> 00:04:05,800
So it looks pretty silly if he's wearing all of this together.
所以如果他所有这些都一起戴上，看起来挺傻的。

83
00:04:05,800 --> 00:04:07,120
All right.
好的。

84
00:04:07,120 --> 00:04:13,960
And so those four key items, those four key pieces of clothing are for our language takeaway
所以这四个关键物品，这四件关键衣物就是我们今天“语言要点”

85
00:04:13,960 --> 00:04:14,960
today.
的内容。

86
00:04:14,960 --> 00:04:18,600
Why don't we listen to this dialogue again, and we'll come back soon to talk about Fluency
我们为什么不把这段对话再听一遍呢？我们很快会回来讨论“流利度

87
00:04:18,600 --> 00:04:19,600
Builder.
构建”。

88
00:04:19,600 --> 00:04:20,600
Bye, mom.
再见，妈妈。

89
00:04:20,600 --> 00:04:21,600
Wait, Jimmy, it's cold outside.
等等，Jimmy，外面很冷。

90
00:04:21,600 --> 00:04:22,600
Put a hat on.
戴上帽子。

91
00:04:22,600 --> 00:04:23,600
Okay, bye.
好的，再见。

92
00:04:23,600 --> 00:04:24,600
No, wait, you'll be too cold without mittens.
不，等等，不戴连指手套你会太冷的。

93
00:04:24,600 --> 00:04:33,480
All right, see ya.
好吧，回头见。

94
00:04:33,480 --> 00:04:35,800
Hold on, with that wind you're gonna catch a cold.
等一下，刮着风，你会感冒的。

95
00:04:35,800 --> 00:04:36,800
Wear this scarf.
戴上这条围巾。

96
00:04:36,800 --> 00:04:38,680
Okay, see you after school.
好的，放学后见。

97
00:04:38,680 --> 00:04:41,120
Oh, and earmuffs, put these on.
哦，还有耳罩，戴上这个。

98
00:04:41,120 --> 00:04:42,120
Here we go.
好了。

99
00:04:42,120 --> 00:04:43,120
Mom?
妈妈？

100
00:04:43,120 --> 00:04:44,120
Yes, honey?
怎么了，亲爱的？

101
00:04:44,120 --> 00:04:45,120
I can't breathe.
我喘不过气了。

102
00:04:45,120 --> 00:04:46,120
All right, we're back.
好了，我们回来了。

103
00:04:46,120 --> 00:04:56,640
So now let's take a look at four key phrases on Fluency Builder.
那现在我们来看看“流利度构建”里的四个关键短语。

104
00:04:56,640 --> 00:04:57,640
Fluency Builder.
流利度构建。

105
00:04:57,640 --> 00:05:03,240
Okay, this first phrase, as I said before, has to do with the mom and the boy saying
好的，第一个短语，就像我之前说的，跟妈妈和男孩互相

106
00:05:03,240 --> 00:05:04,840
goodbye to each other.
告别有关。

107
00:05:04,840 --> 00:05:07,840
So he says, all right, see ya.
所以他说，好吧，回头见。

108
00:05:07,840 --> 00:05:08,840
See ya.
回头见。

109
00:05:08,840 --> 00:05:09,840
Ya.
见。

110
00:05:09,840 --> 00:05:12,440
Okay, so see as in to look, to, right?
好的，所以“see”是看的意思，对吧？

111
00:05:12,440 --> 00:05:13,840
You see something.
你看东西。

112
00:05:13,840 --> 00:05:14,840
And what about Y-A-Y?
那Y-A-Y呢？

113
00:05:14,840 --> 00:05:15,840
Ya.
见。

114
00:05:15,840 --> 00:05:19,560
Okay, so this is a very spoken language way of saying you.
好的，这是一种非常口语化的说法，表示“你”。

115
00:05:19,560 --> 00:05:24,840
So we could say, see you later, but if you want to make it shorter, you can say, see
所以我们可以说“see you later”，但如果你想缩短，可以说“see

116
00:05:24,840 --> 00:05:25,840
ya.
ya”。

117
00:05:25,840 --> 00:05:26,840
See ya.
回头见。

118
00:05:26,840 --> 00:05:27,840
Bye.
拜拜。

119
00:05:27,840 --> 00:05:28,840
Bye, goodbye.
拜拜，再见。

120
00:05:28,840 --> 00:05:29,840
All right, so see ya.
好的，所以是“回头见”。

121
00:05:29,840 --> 00:05:32,080
And then what's our next way of saying goodbye?
那我们下一个说再见的方式是什么？

122
00:05:32,080 --> 00:05:33,080
Hold on.
等一下。

123
00:05:33,080 --> 00:05:34,080
Oh, wait, that's...
哦，等等，那是……

124
00:05:34,080 --> 00:05:36,080
We're not there yet.
我们还没到那一步。

125
00:05:36,080 --> 00:05:39,960
No, hold on is our next phrase and this is a way to say wait.
不，“hold on”是我们的下一个短语，这是一种说“等等”的方式。

126
00:05:39,960 --> 00:05:41,480
Wait, hold on.
等等，等一下。

127
00:05:41,480 --> 00:05:44,000
So you just say hold on, it means wait.
所以你只要说“hold on”，它的意思就是“等等”。

128
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:45,160
It's not really rude, right?
这不算很粗鲁，对吧？

129
00:05:45,160 --> 00:05:46,520
It's just a little bit more casual.
只是稍微随意一点。

130
00:05:46,520 --> 00:05:47,520
Exactly.
没错。

131
00:05:47,520 --> 00:05:48,520
It's very casual.
非常随意。

132
00:05:48,520 --> 00:05:49,520
So you cannot say hold.
所以你不能只说“hold”。

133
00:05:49,520 --> 00:05:51,960
That doesn't make sense.
那说不通。

134
00:05:51,960 --> 00:05:54,900
You have to use these two words together.
你必须把这两个词一起用。

135
00:05:54,900 --> 00:05:55,900
Hold on.
等一下。

136
00:05:55,900 --> 00:06:00,200
So like I said before with Marco who wants to go fast, I could say, hold on.
就像我之前跟想走快的Marco说的，我可以说“hold on”。

137
00:06:00,200 --> 00:06:01,200
Wait a second.
等一下。

138
00:06:01,200 --> 00:06:02,200
All right.
好的。

139
00:06:02,200 --> 00:06:03,200
Okay, so hold on.
好的，所以“hold on”。

140
00:06:03,200 --> 00:06:04,200
See ya.
再见。

141
00:06:04,200 --> 00:06:08,040
And now you got to be careful because you're going to catch a cold.
现在你得小心了，因为你会感冒的。

142
00:06:08,040 --> 00:06:10,000
To catch a cold.
感冒。

143
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:17,360
Okay, so a cold is when you cough, you have a sore throat, it's starting to get cold outside
好的，感冒就是你咳嗽、喉咙痛，外面开始变冷，

144
00:06:17,360 --> 00:06:18,960
and you don't feel well.
而且你感觉不舒服。

145
00:06:18,960 --> 00:06:21,320
So you have a runny nose.
所以你流鼻涕。

146
00:06:21,320 --> 00:06:23,080
It's an illness.
这是一种病。

147
00:06:23,080 --> 00:06:24,920
And most people get this every year.
大多数人每年都会得一次。

148
00:06:24,920 --> 00:06:26,480
It's very common.
这很常见。

149
00:06:26,480 --> 00:06:30,040
But you don't get a cold, you catch a cold.
但你不是“得到”感冒，你是“染上”感冒。

150
00:06:30,040 --> 00:06:35,680
So catch is the same word we use for when we talk about sports like throwing and catching.
所以“catch”这个词和我们谈论运动时用的“扔和接”是同一个词。

151
00:06:35,680 --> 00:06:37,760
It's almost like it just hits you.
就好像它突然击中了你。

152
00:06:37,760 --> 00:06:38,760
It's so fast.
它来得太快了。

153
00:06:38,760 --> 00:06:39,920
You just catch a cold.
你只是染上了感冒。

154
00:06:39,920 --> 00:06:43,040
So that's really important what you just said because you don't use the verb get.
你刚才说的这点很重要，因为你不用动词“get”。

155
00:06:43,040 --> 00:06:44,480
You don't get a cold.
你不是“得到”感冒。

156
00:06:44,480 --> 00:06:46,000
You catch a cold.
你是“染上”感冒。

157
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:50,520
Or if you say that you were sick last week because you had a cold, you would say, oh,
或者如果你说你上周因为感冒生病了，你会说，哦，

158
00:06:50,520 --> 00:06:52,960
I caught a cold or I had a cold.
我染上了感冒，或者我得了感冒。

159
00:06:52,960 --> 00:06:53,960
Exactly.
没错。

160
00:06:53,960 --> 00:06:58,400
So remember present tense, I catch a cold.
所以记住现在时：我染上感冒。

161
00:06:58,400 --> 00:07:00,920
Past tense, I caught a cold last week.
过去时：我上周染上了感冒。

162
00:07:00,920 --> 00:07:01,920
Okay.
好的。

163
00:07:01,920 --> 00:07:05,240
And our last phrase for fluency builder is here we go.
我们流利度提升的最后一个短语是“here we go”。

164
00:07:05,240 --> 00:07:06,240
Here we go.
开始吧。

165
00:07:06,240 --> 00:07:07,240
Okay, so when do we hear this phrase?
好的，那我们什么时候听到这个短语？

166
00:07:07,240 --> 00:07:10,920
So the mother says to the boy, put these on, here we go.
所以妈妈对男孩说：“戴上这些，好了。”

167
00:07:10,920 --> 00:07:12,720
So she's doing something with him.
所以她正在帮他做点什么。

168
00:07:12,720 --> 00:07:15,600
She's helping him put his earmuffs on.
她在帮他戴上耳罩。

169
00:07:15,600 --> 00:07:18,600
And here we go is a way to say, okay, I've finished.
